The article announces several nominations and appointments made by the President of the United States. The nominations include Bridget A. Brink to be the Ambassador Extraordinary and Plenipotentiary of the United States of America to the Slovak Republic, Ada E. Brown to be a United States District Judge for the Northern District of Texas, John Jefferson Daigle to be the Ambassador Extraordinary and Plenipotentiary of the United States of America to the Republic of Cabo Verde, Matthew S. Klimow to be the Ambassador Extraordinary and Plenipotentiary of the United States of America to Turkmenistan, Christopher Landau to be the Ambassador Extraordinary and Plenipotentiary of the United States of America to the United Mexican States, and David John Novak to be a United States District Judge for the Eastern District of Virginia. In addition, Jeffrey A. Rosen has been nominated to be the Deputy Attorney General, replacing Rod J. Rosenstein.